    • name

      public javafx.beans.property.ReadOnlyStringProperty nameProperty

      Returns the property containing the name of this UINode.

      1. The name is only used for UI purposes, such as being displayed in a tooltip upon a user hovering over the button for this UINode.
      2. To change the actual button for this UINode, see buttonIDProperty().

    • UINode

      public UINode​(net.rgielen.fxweaver.core.FxWeaver weaver, org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext ctx, String name, String buttonID, Function<UINode,​UIPage<?>> coverPageFunction, Runnable onAction)

    • UINode

      public UINode​(net.rgielen.fxweaver.core.FxWeaver weaver, org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext ctx, String name, String buttonID, Function<UINode,​UIPage<?>> coverPageFunction, Runnable onAction, javafx.scene.layout.StackPane contentPane)

      Fully parameterized constructor for UINode objects.


      Parameters:
      weaver - The FxWeaver instance to be used for linking UINode JavaFX attributes to Spring.
      • See Springable.weaver()
      ctx - The ApplicationContext that allows easy access to Spring-related functionality for this UINode.
      • See Springable.ctx()
      name - The name to be assigned to this UINode.
      • See nameProperty()
      buttonID - The ID mapped to the cached image to be used as the button for this UINode.

      coverPageFunction - The Function that will retrieve the UIPage to be used as the cover page of this UINode.
      • If the specified Function is null, a DummyPage will be used as the cover page instead.
      onAction - A Runnable that will be executed when the button for this UINode is pressed.
      • See ImageButton.initialize() for exact implementation.
      contentPane - The StackPane in which the contents (pages) of this UINode are displayed.
      • Accessed via getContent().getDisplayContainer()
